# Everything the build does not need, and two things it must never have.
#
# The build context is uploaded to the daemon before the first line of the
# Dockerfile runs, so a fat context is slow even when every layer is cached.

node_modules
dist
data
data-test-*

.git
.github
*.md

.claude
.env
.env.*

# And the two that matter:
#
#   .env - a secret, which would be baked into an image layer forever. Deleting it
#          in a later RUN does not remove it; layers are immutable and anybody with
#          the image can read it back out. There is no un-committing a secret into
#          a container image.
#
#   .git - the entire history of the repository, including every secret anybody
#          has ever committed and then removed. Shipping it is how a rotated key
#          gets un-rotated.
